            "ratingValue": "5",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "The character and atmosphere of the school is remarkable. Excellent faculty members and top class services are provided. The outcome is highly satisfactory. It was set up on Ist March, 1836. It was founded by Major General Claude Martin. It is affiliated with the Council for the Indian School Certificate Examinations. It is an uppermost English medium and private school. It is regulated by the Anglican Church of North India. It is mentioned that philanthropist Martin left a large portion of his wealth for the founding of such schools in his will.",
          "publisher": {
